Welcome to §9§9§9§b§b§b§b§b§b§l§l§l§l§l§lSupersymmetry§r§r§r§r§r§r! 

You have just landed on an unfamiliar planet. This book will teach you how to rebuild civilization from scratch in only §k4200§r pages.

Start by getting a rock§r. This book is interactive.

When you pick up a rock from the ground, press the §l§l§l§l§l§l§a§a§a§a§a§aSUBMIT§r button to complete the quest and continue.

If you lose this book, you can check the quests by pressing the §2§aGRAVE §rkey.

----------------------------------------
§3WELCOME TO SUPERSYMMETRY!
§r----------------------------------------
- Explore your surroundings
§r- Find shelter
- Prepare for the winter
- Acquire basic resources
- Try not to die
------------------------------------

It is probably impossible to try to play GregTech without using JEI. So here are some tips on how to use JEI to its full potential.

§eBookmark items regularly§r (default key §aA§r) so you don't have to type the names over and over.

Most of the items have §emultiple recipes§r! Dont stop at the first recipe and think that item is impossible.
Sometimes a material is only available from §etiny dusts§r, sometimes it's available from a §efluid solution§r. It takes some practice. Oil processing and nuclear chemistry are pretty bad about this.

You can §epress @§r to see only items from that mod. For example, if you search for §c@gregtech§r, you will only see items from GregTech.

You can §epress $ §rto see only items from a specific entry in the Ore Dictionary. For example, if you search for §c$logWood§r, you will only see wooden logs.

You can §epress U §ron an item to see its uses.
betterquesting:10.name:8: It's JEI, not NEI. Use it wisely.

betterquesting:10.desc:8:
You are only able to grow some crops in certain seasons (but you can change that using a §agreenhouse§r, or with automated farming), and the environment around you will change throughout the year.

§aSpring §rstarts on March 1 and ends on May 30.
§6Summer §rstarts on June 1 and ends on August 30.
§cAutumn §rstarts on September 1 and ends on November 30.
§bWinter §rstarts on December 1 and ends on February 30.

Flint shards§r are needed to get yourself some tools. 

Gravel can be mined without a tool, and enables you to acquire flint.

Flint can be knapped [§aRight Click while looking at stone§r] on an exposed stone surface, obtaining flint shards.
The Akashic Tome is a compendium of several other guidebooks that might be useful for you. You can get it for free by clicking the checkbox.

Your new Flint Knife can be used for cutting things, making things into shards, or getting §aplant fibers§r§.. 

You can also use the flint knife as a weapon.

You can use your shiny new §eflint knife§r to make plant fibers. 

You can get §aplant fibers§r by breaking §2tall grass §rwith your flint knife.
You can pack those §aplant fibers§r into §aplant string§r.
Construct a §6Flint Hatchet§r using flint and plant fibers. As the name implies, it can cut down trees.
betterquesting:10.name:8: The part where you get wood

betterquesting:10.desc:8: You can use flint to develop new §6weapons§r. All you can make right now are a bow and an arrow, but they'll suffice for now.
Using our §6crafting table §ryou can now construct better tools, a §6flint pickaxe §rfor mining ores and a §6flint shovel §rfor digging sand or gravel.

There are many useful resources underground, so you should be looking around for them. 

Something you need to look for is §l§amagnetite§r. It will be used in the construction of magnets later.

Magnetite is found in ore deposits§a §runderground. Ore deposits are about 20 x 20 meters in size.

If you see a §atiny pile of magnetite §ron the surface, it will indicate that there is a deposit underground. 


Ore deposits can be found every 50 meters or so in each direction. If you are above an ore deposit, you will see metal rocks on the ground and an indicator on the top left of the screen.
Leather can be crafted into armor using a Crafting Table.

The furnace §ris a very primitive smelting device that allows you to cook things up to a temperature of §c1,000 §rK (727° C), just enough to smelt copper, lead §rand §7tin§.§r.

§rMore information on finding these ores is on the next page.
For now you can just make the furnace.

Copper is found in §6Chalcopyrite, Chalcocite, Malachite, Bornite, Tetrahedrite, §ror §6Copper Ore§r deposits. Copper can be found pretty much everywhere in the Earth's crust, and even in the deeper layers.

If you are having trouble finding a specific deposit, look it up in the JEI database, you will find a page showing where it is found. 

Let's start by getting 20 copper ingots.

Finding a §6Tiny Pile of Copper Dust §ron the ground means that there is a deposit under it.

Tin can be found in §6Cassiterite Sand§r, §6Cassiterite Ore§r§r§r, §rand §6Tin Ore§r deposits. You can look them up in the JEI database to see where you can find them.

Tin is a silvery-coloured metal. Tin is soft enough to be cut with little force and a bar of tin can be bent with little effort. 
§6
§l§rOre deposits cover a surface of 20 by 20 meters across. Each deposit can contain up to 5,000 ingots worth of ore.
The §amortar§r§r can be used for crushing ores and ingots into §bdusts§r. You can use stone and flint to make it.

§6Bronze§r is an alloy consisting of 75% copper combined with about 25% tin.

Mix the dusts in a §acrafting table§r in a 3 to 1 ratio to make §6bronze dust§r. Then you must smelt it in a furnace to get bronze ingots.

§3This will unlock Tier 1.

Nights are dark and extremely dangerous on most planets known to support life, seek shelter as soon as possible.

If you go outside, you may notice that there are several entities around you. At this stage you are nowhere near ready for killing any of them, so you must hide.

A grindstone can be used for extracting more dust out of your ores. It's not that good... but it's a start. It's also §cmanual§r, so you have to power it using your hands.

Put a §6Wooden Crank §ron the grindstone and §aright click §ron it to rotate it. After a few seconds, the ore will have turned into dust.

Putting 1 ore in results in an output of 2 dusts.
Breaking leaves§r with a piece of Flint§r or a Flint Knife will drop a stick.

The §7Coke Oven §ris a hollow 3x3x3 structure made of Coke Bricks with a Coke Oven Controller in the center.
It turns §7Coal §rinto §7Coal Coke§r, and Logs into Charcoal.

Coal Coke burns longer in furnaces, and in small coal boilers. 

§3

§rMore advanced tools will be needed to progress towards the Industrial Age. There are six major types of tools.

The §2hammer §ris used kind of everywhere. It's used to make all the other tools and it turns ingots into plates
The §2file§r turns ingots into rods.
The §2saw §rturns wood planks into slabs, and turns logs into 4 planks. Finally!
The §2screwdriver§r is used in most recipes and in setting up covers. It also makes important parts like gears and rotors.
The §2wrench§r is used in cutting pipes and it's probably the most important tools out of all of them.
The §2wire cutter§r cuts wiring.

§lSometimes, JEI shows that you need darmstadtium, or aluminum tools. This is a bug, and recipes accept all kinds of tools.§r

A furnace is not really good for smelting items. Its maximum temperature is only 1000 K (730°C), which is not hot enough for iron.

A Primitive Blast Furnace is made out of 36 §cFirebricks§r. You need to make a §a3x4x3 structure§r§r of firebricks that is hollowed out in the middle. For more help, look at the §cStructure Preview§r in the JEI database.

The Primitive Blast Furnace allows you to smelt iron, wrought iron and §bsteel§r. It has a maximum temperature of about 1400 K (1,127°C).

Like many other structures, it is possible to share the walls of multiple Primitive Blast Furnaces and they will still work.

§l§e§lNOTE: Making the Primitive Blast Furnace requires a steam compressor and a steam macerator. Please check the Industrial Age chapter to continue.

§7Sphalerite §rveins contain §7sphalerite ore§r, an important source of zinc. It's found on Earth at altitude 0 to 60, but also in the deepest part of the crust.

Zinc is a slightly brittle metal at room temperature and has a shiny-greyish appearance.

Zincwill be used to create magnets, but if you can't find zinc, §amagnetite ore §rcan be used instead.

To make magnets, you must have a §bVoltaic Pile§r. §c
§r
A Voltaic Pile is made of three components: a §6Copper Plate§r, a §7Zinc Plate§r, and Electrolyte Paper.

A common electrolyte is §6citric acid§r (found in lemons and limes).

To proceed, we will need §liron§r. Lots of it.
There are multiple ores that contain iron, and these are:

§6Magnetite
Pyrite§r§6
Hematite
Yellow Limonite
Brown Limonite
§6Basaltic Mineral Sand
Granitic Mineral Sand
§ror just §6Iron Ore§r.

They're pretty common veins. Let's get 32 ingots of iron.

To start, you will need a §chot iron rod§r - smelt a normal iron ingot in a furnace, then make it into a rod (with the file).

There are two ways of making magnets:

- Putting a hot iron rod with a §cmagnetite chunk§r in a crafting table, 
- or using the §cvoltaic pile §ralong with some §ccopper fine wire§r (you need special equipment though).§ 

This process is only done once§r. A newly-formed §cmagnetic iron rod § can be used to magnetise other hot iron rodsm so don't throw it out!

§3This will unlock the Industrial Age.
§7Magnetite §rores can be broken up into §7magnetite chunks§r by using a Crafting Table.

We can make better tools out of §6bronze§r. You need to make the tool parts first, and then assemble the tool.

The bronze axe can cut down entire trees with just one click.

The bronze mining hammer can mine an entire 3x3 meter area with one click, unless you're pressing §aSHIFT§r.
Use your new alloy to make a §6bronze sword§r.

Your Primitive Blast Furnace can turn iron ingots into §l§esteel§r, by smelting them with coal coke. 

Making steel is one of the top priorities of the Industrial Age, because you will need §la lot §rof it. Make sure to have your Primitive Blast Furnace running at all times, or try to make 4 Primitive Blast Furnaces sharing their walls.

§rCongratulations, you made it!§r You completed the Primitive Age. Your goal for the Industrial Age is to obtain steam machines, making vacuum tubes and getting electricity.

The following information will be critical to your survival, so read it carefully!


§l§nHow do I get steam?§r

There are different ways to produce steam, there is the §c§cCoal Boiler§r,§c Lava Boiler§r, the §cSolar Boiler§r, and the §cLarge Boilers§r. We can't make them right now so we'll start with the coal boiler.
The Coal Boiler is powered by §cfurnace fuels§r and is extremely fuel efficient. It will take some time to heat up, and once hot enough it will §c§rconsume water§r and §c§rautomatically output steam§r into connected pipes. Remember that boilers can §4§l§nexplode§r when they're already hot, have no water and you add some water.

§l§nHow do Steam machines work?§r

§n§l§rSteam machines are §6slow§r, §6need pipe connection§r, and §6do not auto-output§r.
They also have an §6exhaust vent§r, represented by a gray square on their backside by default. 
This vent can be moved using a wrench, but §6must remain unblocked§r. 
When a recipe is completed, the vent will start shooting steam particles in the air, and if you're standing near the vent, you will be §c§lboiled alive!

§r----------------------------------------------
§3THE INDUSTRIAL AGE HAS BEEN UNLOCKED. GOOD LUCK!
§r----------------------------------------------
§r- Industrialize
- Use the power of steam
- Start producing electricity
- Create the most basic electronics

Tier : 1 
EU/t : 0 
------------------------------------

The §l§rSteam Alloy Smelter §rdirectly combines dusts or ingots into §c§lnew alloys.

§rThis machine requires a fair amount of steam to work. If you ever run out of steam, turn this machine off with a §aSoft Hammer§r and let steam build up again.

The §6Alloy Smelter§r can make bronze for you directly, using §dingots§o§o§r, dusts, or even nuggets.§r You can make a nugget mold as well to turn ingots into nuggets. This machine might also come in handy when processing raw rubber.

NOTE: Like all steam machines, the output port doubles as a steam outlet when recipes complete. §cIt must not be blocked§r. Also, steam is hot, remember? Change the output side by whacking the Alloy Smelter with a wrench.

The §6Steam Macerator §ris used to convert ores into crushed ores. This is the most simple way of doing ore processing.
Every ore you put into the Steam Macerator turns into 2 crushed ores, that can be smelted in the furnace to get two ingots.

Making the macerator will require §bdiamonds§r, which are found in graphite deposits. You can check JEI to see where they are.

§6Molds§o§r can be used in the alloy smelter and the fluid solidifier. You need them to make vacuum tubes.
They can be used for turning dusts into ingots, or ingots into gears, using the alloy smelter.§r
§6Cupronickel §ris required to advance to the next section of the Industrial Age. This alloy can only be made in an alloy smelter, and it's made with one part copper and one part nickel.
betterquesting:10.name:8: I swear to God it's not Constantan

betterquesting:10.desc:8: §6Brass §ris made out of §6three dusts of copper §rand §7one of zinc§r in a crafting table. Smelt it in a furnace to get the ingot.

§dNickel§r is found in §6Garnierite§r, §6Pentlandite§r, §6§rand plain old §6Nickel §rores. They are found in the Beneath.

It will be required for the next milestone (§6electricity§r), so let's start mining.
§7Tin Alloy§r§r pipes are needed for making Vacuum in Gregicality: Science. Gregicality changes normal progression so that vacuums are required to make vacuum tubes.
The §aSteam Compressor §rcompresses things. It can turn ingots into blocks, as well as nuggets to ingots.

The §l§r§6Steam Forge Hammer §ris an extremely useful machine that will do pretty much any recipe that requires a hammer.

§r§r§r§l§rIt can make §6plates §r§l§rat a better ratio, only requiring 1.5 ingots instead of 2 per plate.

To make vacuum tubes, we will need §a§9Cobalt§r. Cobaltite is found in Nickel veins in the Beneath, at Y levels 0 to 250.

Smelting 1 Cobaltite Ore will give you 3 nuggets of Cobalt.

§cRed Alloy§r is a highly conductive alloy made out of redstone and §ecopper§r. It can only be made in the alloy smelter.

You can find §4Redstone Ore §rin the overworld, at Y levels 15 to 35. If you find redstone rocks on the surface, this means that there will be a deposit underground. Let's get digging!

Congratulations, [INSERT PLAYER NAME HERE]! You made it past the easy part. Now it's time for the hard part.  

As I said in the beginning quest, the main objective of the Industrial Age is §evacuum tubes§r, which are kind of complicated and confusing to set up.
Our first step is making §aglass tubes§r, with a ball mold and glass dust.

It's time to start constructing the first piece of circuitry, the §aVacuum Tube§r. To make the components we will need §6Gold§r (or §eGlowstone§r, if you've been to the Nether), some steel and some copper.

To make vacuum tubes, we must obviously get vacuum. The easiest way to make it in the Steam Age is by using §6vacuum ejectors§r.

Vacuum ejectors are a clever machine that makes vacuum only by §6using steam§r. The Steam Ejector requires §6steel§r, so make sure to build a Blast Furnace before continuing.

The Steam Ejector will consume steam and lower its pressure down to §6130uPa§r (0.00013Pa) over time. Vacuum Tubes will require the §6Vacuum Chamber§r to be produced. You have to hook up the §6Output Side §rof the Steam Ejector to the Vacuum Chamber to make it work.

The Steam Ejector will not blow things up. However c§6onnecting a pressurized container§r to something that cannot handle that pressure will cause and §cimplosion§r (if it's under the required pressure) or §cexplosion§r (if it's over), so be careful!
§6Kovar §ris an alloy of §1Cobalt§r, §7Iron §rand §8Nickel §rthat is required for making the Vacuum Tubes. It can be smelted in a furnace.

If you want to make more advanced (also cheaper!) circuits you will need a §6cleanroom§r. 

The cleanroom is a multiblock between 3x4x3 and 15x15x15 (WxHxL) blocks. You will need to place §6plascrete§o§r blocks on all sides, a §acontroller§r in the top center, §bfilter machine casings§r for all blocks on the top, and energy and maintenance hatches.

When at 100% efficiency, the cleanroom drains 4 EU/t. However, while it's charging up to that value (0% through 99%), the cleanroom will drain 40 EU/t. For this reason, it is recommended to have at least two amps of LV feeding into an LV energy hatch (or 1 amp of anything higher than LV feeding into an appropriate energy hatch). 

§c§c§cRecipes start running when the cleanroom is >90% clean. §r§r§rDoing a "Needs Cleanroom" recipe in a cleanroom without 100% efficiency can potentially slow down recipe times or make them progress backwards. Be absolutely sure that your cleanroom is running at 100% efficiency.

============================
The Cleanroom requires:

- 1 Cleanroom Controller
- 1 HV Energy Hatch
- 1 HV Machine Hull
- 1 Fluid Passthrough Hatch
- 1 Item Passthrough Hatch
- 1 HV Diode
- 1 Maintenance Hatch
- 6 Cleanroom Glass
- 75 Plascrete
- 8 Filter Casing
- 2 Iron Doors

The §bBottling Machine§r is a 3x2x3 multi-block. It is used to fill liquid containers.

The Bottling Machine requires:

3 Steel Scaffolding
2 Iron Sheetmetal
1 Redstone Engineering Block
2 Light Engineering Blocks
3 Conveyor Belts
1 Fluid Pump
1 Glass

You can check the §6Engineer's Manual§r for help. The guide on the bottling machine is in the §7§6Simple Machinery §rchapter.

After putting together the structure, whack the middle conveyor with the §6Engineer's Hammer §rto form the multiblock.
If the bottling machine doesn't form, you may try switching the order of the conveyors. 

The Bottling Machine has no GUI. Redstone Flux is supplied on the §6top-right§r block of the multi-block (where the Light Engineering Block was).
If you cannot get fluid to go in the machine, try putting a tank near it and using a §7LV Pump §rand fluid pipes to transfer the fluid.

Fluids are added through the bottom-middle block of the backside. Items are added by dropping them on the Bottling Machine's Conveyor Belts. When a liquid storing item (such as a Bucket or Jerrycan) is introduced to the Bottling Machine, the Bottling Machine will fill and output it, consuming some RF.

{ResourceLocation:supersymmetry:guides/ie-bottler.png}

We'll need a §amotor §rto generate electricity. Let's make one.

§cNOTE: In later stages of the pack, you will need to make a LOT of motors. You should start crafting a batch of motors instead of just one, to reduce the pain.

Our first option for electricity right now is §6kinetic energy§r. You can make it with a §6kinetic dynamo§r.

You can attach a §ewindmill §ror a §bwaterwheel §rto your kinetic dynamo. We'll explain those in a later quest.

The §bWater Wheel§r must be connected to a §3flowing water stream§r in order to work, and the amount of power produced scales directly with the number of flowing water blocks adjacent to the wheel. 

The maximum amount of power that a Water Wheel can produce is §c30 RF/t§r, which arises from a water source flowing "in a semi-circle from the top down one side and along the bottom."

You can put up to three Water Wheels on one dynamo to maximize energy output.

The §eWindmill§r generates §cRF§r using the power of the wind. The power output can be improved by using a §eWindmill Sail§r on the hub to cover a single blade in fabric. The Windmill reaches maximum output (§c35 RF/t§r) once all 8 blades are improved this way. The Windmill also generates more power when it's raining or thundering.

The §d§cThermoelectric Generator§r generates §cRF§r based on the temperature difference of the blocks surrounding it.

The §chigh-temperature§r and §blow-temperature§r blocks need to be across from each other. For example, you can put a block of water and a block of lava right next to the generator,

Finally, this is the last step of the vacuum tube chain!
You just need to combine the 3 things together.

Place the Glass Tube, the Kovar Ring and the vacuum tube parts in the §6Pressure Chamber§r. It must be pressurized at a vacuum of 130 uPa, or the recipe won't work.

Macerating is still an ore doubler like in other mods, but there is a twist, it does not give dusts directly! Crushed Ores are meant for more advanced ore processing. One Crushed Ore will convert to one dust.

To get the Impure Dust§r, hammer the Crushed Ore. 

This is done either by using a Hammer tool in the crafting table, or using the Steam Forge Hammer.

The Impure Dust can be smelted in the Furnace to get the Ingot, however mixed ores (Limonite, Chalcopyrite) will only give nuggets over ingots.

The Impure Dust can also be thrown in a vanilla Cauldron filled with water to clean it and turn it into a regular dust. Throw them in full stacks to consume less water per single dust.

§lNote: Macerating, hammering, and then smelting (sometimes into nuggets) is really time consuming in the steam age! Resource efficiency can be ignored for now. Nobody will blame you for smelting ores directly into ingots.

GregTech's §ehigh pressure §rsteam machines require steel and they're two times faster than normal steam machines. Let's make a Steel Hull to get started.

You can also make high pressure §r§eboilers§r to generate steam twice as fast.
We can also use §4lava §rto boil steam. Let's make a Lava Boiler.

§6Solar boilers §rcan be used to get steam, for free, using the power of the sun. 
But there's a catch: they only work while the sun is up, 13 hours per day.

This pack has 2 different options for tanks:

- §6GregTech Drums§o§r: they can be made of various materials

- §6Industrial Renewal tanks§r: they are harder to build, but they can contain more fluid.

For now, let's make a GregTech bronze drum.
A MV circuit assembler is needed to make Micro circuits, the next GregTech circuit line.
In the Industrial Age you are able to produce better weapons. The §aHandcannon §ris one of those. It uses stone bullets for ammunition.

The §aDouble Barrel Shotgun§r is the first ever gun that you can make. It uses §aShotgun Rounds §o§rfor ammo.

It's a shotgun, this means it will shoot 8 times at once. For more info, look at the tooltip.
The §TTechGuns revolver uses §6Pistol Rounds §rfor ammo.
Resistors are another major component of §bLV circuits§r. They are made with sticky resin, which can be found on §2rubber trees§r, or you can get it by smelting slimeballs.

§6Coated circuit boards§r are another component of LV circuits. They are made with sticky resin, and wood planks.

You have to coat the board with wires to make it usable, turning it into a §6Basic Circuit Board§r.

Assembling the circuit parts (§6resistors§r, §bvacuum tubes§r, §cwiring§r, and the §2board§r) gets you one Primitive Circuit. 

Circuits are the brain of all GregTech machines - they're needed for the machine to work. This modpack has over 10 different tiers of circuits, ranging all the way from a simple tube on a wood plank all the way to a 200 step reality bending supracausal circuit.

The §bMetal Press§r is a 3x1x3 multi-block. It is used to mold metals, and it makes plates at a higher efficiency.

The Metal Press requires:

2 Steel Scaffoldings
1 Redstone Engineering Block
1 Piston
1 Heavy Engineering Block
2 Conveyor Belts

You can check the §6Engineer's Manual§r for help. The guide on the metal press is in the §7§6Simple Machinery §rchapter.

After putting together the structure, whack the middle conveyor with the §6Engineer's Hammer §rto form the multiblock.
Items are added by dropping them onto the structure. Right-clicking (a Metal Press with a Mold will attach the Mold to the Metal Press. The mold can be detached by shift right-clicking with an Engineer's Hammer.

{ResourceLocation:supersymmetry:guides/ie-metalpress.png}

The §6Tesla Coil§r protects a 13x13x13 area by shocking mobs that enter the area. 
In order to protect the area, the Tesla Coil needs to consume §c256 RF/t§r, and needs to consume 512 RF each time it shocks a mob.

The Tesla Coil must be powered by §cRedstone§r in order to function. This can be inverted by right-clicking the Tesla Coil with an Engineer's Hammer.
The Tesla Coil's §6electricity damage§r will cook animal meat, but it will not create charged creepers.

By default, the Tesla Coil is in high-power mode. §2Shift-clicking §rthe coil will turn it into low-power mode, which consumes half the power but with only half the range. If you change the mode of the coil while it's active, you will §c§ndie instantly.§r

Wearing a §bFaraday suit§r near a low-power Tesla Coil will prevent any damage being caused to the user, but wearing a Faraday suit near a high-power Tesla Coil will increase the damage.

Don't like your enemies? We have a solution for you!

The Industrial Renewal(TM) §6Electric Fence §rwill roast any player or mob that comes into contact with it.

This pack has two different types of electricity: §cRF (Redstone Flux) §rand §bEU (Energy Units)§r§r. What we are going to use in the Industrial Age is RF. 

In the next tier, we will unlock EU and GregTech machines, and we will explain the EU system in more detail there.

Remember that 16 RF equals 1 EU, and if GregTech machines get a higher voltage that they can handle, they will explode. To convert between RF and EU you will need to use energy converters. 

------------------
To store RF, you need to make a §cLow Voltage Capacitor. §r
To transfer RF, you need to use §cLow Voltage RF wire§r. Make a LV Wire Coil, and connect it to a LV Wire Connector to transfer the energy.

Don't get confused between Immersive Engineering electricity and GregTech electricity. Immersive Engineering LV and GregTech LV are two completely different things, so don't mix them up.
Immersive Engineering's §6conveyors §rcan be used for moving things around in your base. You can change the orientation of a Conveyor using the §6Engineer's Hammer§r.

Circuits in Gregicality are defined by two characteristics: their §6technological level§r (electronic, quantum, optical, etc,) and their "rank" in a given §6technology tier§r (assembly, mainframe, etc.)

These two characteristics give a circuit its name and voltage tier (e.g. the Micro Computer, an EV circuit and the 3rd micro circuit.)

The first technological tier of circuits, primitive circuits, is crafted by hand. The following tiers are fabricated in Circuit Assemblers, or the Assembly Line for high-end assemblies, computers and mainframes. Circuits at the Quantum tier or higher require the Large Circuit Assembly Line, craftable using LuV circuits (the first of which is the Nano Mainframe.)

Higher technological tiers demand more complex processing chains for their respective components, but generally follow similar patterns in terms of what components they require (SMDs, circuit boards, metal frames for mainframes, etc.) Technological advancement will also allow you to make previous circuits more efficiently (e.g. using SoCs to craft Refined Processors without through-hole/SMD components.)

§6Benzene §ris a good source of power in the MV age. One bucket of Benzene gives 288,000 EU, lasting 1:52 minutes in an MV gas turbine, or almost 8 minutes in an LV gas turbine.

Benzene can also be used in an Immersive Engineering gas turbine, or in an IE Steam Boiler.

The §6Cracker Unit §ris a GregTech multiblock that is used to thermally crack heavy hydrocarbons into lighter fractions. This machine allows Light or Heavy Fuel to be further distilled into the lighter fractions, or into the secondary products Toluene and Lubricant more efficiently.

§6Propene §ris another hydrocarbon that you can make using the Cracker Unit. First of all make either Steam-Cracked Light Fuel or Steam-Cracked Naphtha, then distill them into Propene.

§3Don't confuse Propene with Propane. They're NOT the same thing. §r

You can make §6polyethylene §reven easier if you have the Cracking Unit. 

You just have to get Steam Cracked Light Fuel, then distill it to Ethylene, and add oxygen or air to make it Polyethylene.

You can make §dMethane §rin a variety of ways. 

- Combine 4 Hydrogens and 1 Carbon in a Chemical Reactor (not very efficient)
- Centrifuge Rubber Wood or food items
- Get it by distilling oil products (you'll need a Distillation Tower, unlocked at Tier 3)
Some new recipes, like Polytetrafluoroethylene, will need a §dHV Chemical Reactor§r§r. Let's make one.

You can get §3Fluorine§r from electrolyzing §bBlue Topaz§r, §6Topaz§r, §7Bastnasite §rand §dLepidolite§r.

Chloroform is made of Methane and Chlorine. It's used to make Polytetrafluoroethylene, the 3rd tier of plastic in GregTech.

If you need help with getting Methane, look at the Chemistry tab.

§8Hydrofluoric Acid§r is made by combining Hydrogen and Fluorine. 

If you need help with getting Fluorine, look at JEI or the Chemistry tab, you're in Tier 4, I shouldn't be telling you this.

Combine Chloroform and Hydrofluoric Acid to make Tetrafluoroethylene. Then polymerize (blast it with air or oxygen) it to get Polytetrafluoroethylene.

Polytetrafluoroethylene is a really complicated and long name. You can just call it PTFE or Teflon.

If you want to upgrade your Electric Blast Furnace, you'll need Kanthal. It's just an Iron + Aluminum + Nickel alloy.

Remember: when you smelt Kanthal, you'll get a Hot Kanthal Ingot, which you'll need to put in the Quenching Machine to cool it down into a normal Kanthal ingot.

Better materials need higher temperatures. You can just exchange the old coils with the new ones. Kanthal coils let you reach 2700 K, enough to smelt titanium. 

You can even reuse the old Cupronickel coils in other machines like the Cracking Unit or Pyrolyse Oven.

§3This quest unlocks at Tier 3.

Now that we're getting to make hotter materials, we will need to cool them to use them. You can't just touch an ingot of titanium at 2300°C.

Introduce: the Quenching Machine. You may think that this extremely advanced, Tier 4 machine just puts ingots in water, but there are actually multiple quenching fluids for better and faster cooling.

These quenching fluids are:

Water:
    +Very easy to get
    +Moderately fast

Air:
    +Very easy to get
    -Very slow

Compressed Air:
    +Easy to get
    -Slow

Inert gases (Nitrogen):
    +Easy to get
    +Can be used to avoid reaction with water/oxygen
    -Very Slow

Compressed inert gases:
    +Moderately easy to get
    +Can be used to avoid reaction with water/oxygen
    -Slow

Quenching oil:
    +Fast
    +Can be used to avoid reaction with water/oxygen
    -Hard to make

Brine:
    +Very fast
    +Very easy to get
    -Some metals do not like the salt and need washing

It's time for us to get §6titanium§o§r. Titanium is found in §5Bauxite§r, §eand §dRutile §r§rores. Smelting Titanium is quite an involved process, so let's try to get the ores first.
§7Magnesium§r can be obtained by electrolyzing Asbestos, Obsidian, Magnesite, Olivine, Pyrope or Talc. We'll need it for the Titanium smelting process, so let's make some!

Smelting titanium is quite an involved process, and it requires a few steps.
Since you can't electrolyze Titanium Dust out of the ores, we'll have to do a few extra steps.

First of all, put Rutile Dust, Carbon and Chlorine in a chemical reactor, it makes this:

Rutile Dust + Carbon + Chlorine => Carbon Monoxide + §6Titanium Tetrachloride§r

You can obtain Chlorine by electrolyzing a lot of Salt, and you can just void the Carbon Monoxide since it isn't that important at this point.

Put Titanium and Titanium Tetrachloride in an EBF to smelt it.

This makes a Hot Titanium Ingot, that you will then need to quench to turn into a normal Titanium Ingot.
